<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 4: CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER
        HEAD INSPECTION - PRESSURE CHECK CYLINDER HEAD
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="5">
        <title>PRESSURE CHECK CYLINDER HEAD</title>
        <para>Pressure testing the cylinder head will reveal cracks in ports or sleeve leakage which cannot be observed
            using dye penetrant. Pressure-test the cylinder head as follows:
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If removed, install shoulder bolt into cylinder head. Tighten to the special torque value (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600433">4.33</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install fuel injectors into cylinder head injector bores and secure, refer to "Fuel Injector
                Installation" in this section for instructions.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the valves, using a valve spring compressor. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">"CYLINDER HEAD RECONDITIONING</emph>", in this section for valve removal instructions.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1600432" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5263" filename="../figeg5/eg5263.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.32 Identifying Cylinder Head Crack</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600433" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5148" filename="../figeg5/eg5148.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.33 Installing Fuel Injector Shoulder Bolt</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pressure test the cylinder head using the Cylinder Head Pressure Test Plate Kit
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE4289-1A</emph>
                Hardware and Regulator and
                <emph type="bold">ZTSE4289-2A</emph>
                Plate. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600434">4.34</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fasten the pressure plate and head gasket to the cylinder head gasket surface using the
                twenty-four (24) mounting bolts and nuts supplied with the kit. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600435">4.35</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove thermostat and install air regulator. Secure to cylinder head with two (2) mounting
                bolts. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600436">4.36</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the pipe plug next to the thermostat opening. Fill cylinder head with hot water and
                reinstall pipe plug.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a hose fitting to the cylinder head at the removed plug. Apply 124-138 kPa (18-20
                psi) air pressure and visually inspect for leaks at the:
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel injector nozzle sleeve area</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Ports</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Upper deck</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Lower deck</para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>IF LEAKAGE IS OBSERVED AT ANY PORT OR THE UPPER AND LOWER DECK,
                        <emph type="underscr">REPLACE THE CYLINDER HEAD</emph>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef1600434" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg6912" filename="../figeg6/eg6912.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.34 Cylinder Head Pressure Test Kit Components</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">1. Pressure Test Plate</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">2. Air Regulator</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">3. Pressure Test Plate Mounting Bolts (24)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600435" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5399" filename="../figeg5/eg5399.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.35 Mounting Cylinder Head Pressure Test Plate</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef1600436" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg5400" filename="../figeg5/eg5400.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.36 Mounting Air Regulator To Cylinder Head</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">1. Cylinder Head</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">2. Air Regulator</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
